    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains 24 monthly observations (12 months \u00d7 2 years) of synthetic temperature values. Categorical temporal data on the x-axis (months) pairs with continuous interval measurements on the y-axis (\u00b0C). Synthetic data combines: 1) Linear trend (2023 \u03bc=16.4\u00b0C, 2024 \u03bc=18.1\u00b0C \u0394+1.7\u00b0C) 2) Seasonal sinusoid (\u00b15\u00b0C amplitude) 3) Gaussian noise (\u03c3=0.8\u00b0C). The spline chart minimizes visual clutter (Tufte's data-ink ratio) while preserving trend visibility through Cairo's principle of proportional ink. Annotations highlight critical climate events following Bertin's semiology of graphical signs. Dual series coloring (#2980B9=baseline, #E67E22=anomaly) ensures preattentive discrimination of datasets."
